1
00:00:17,025 --> 00:00:18,817
Who is that kid?

2
00:00:18,900 --> 00:00:21,608
[YOSHITOKI] He's from the
Furuta branch of the family.

3
00:00:21,692 --> 00:00:24,608
Their youngest. Intrigued?

4
00:00:24,692 --> 00:00:27,275
Just thinking he has good form.

5
00:00:27,358 --> 00:00:29,983
[YOSHITOKI]
Tsuneyoshi seems to favor him.

6
00:00:30,067 --> 00:00:33,067
Among the illegitimate
children, at least.

7
00:00:33,150 --> 00:00:36,650
But that can only
take him so far.

8
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:39,025
His place is at
the foot of our table.

9
00:02:17,817 --> 00:02:21,067
Nimura dash and slash!

10
00:02:22,733 --> 00:02:24,733
[laughs]

11
00:02:24,817 --> 00:02:27,192
What's the matter?

12
00:02:27,275 --> 00:02:28,358
Ah-ha!

13
00:02:28,442 --> 00:02:30,150
Got you!

14
00:02:31,442 --> 00:02:33,442
So that didn't quite do it.

15
00:02:33,525 --> 00:02:34,483
Oh well.

16
00:02:34,567 --> 00:02:36,275
How about this?

17
00:02:37,483 --> 00:02:39,233
I'm not done yet!

18
00:02:45,942 --> 00:02:47,608
I must confess.

19
00:02:47,692 --> 00:02:49,317
For the sake of
a beautiful duel,

20
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:53,567
I was rather hoping
you'd have a sword.

21
00:02:58,692 --> 00:03:00,400
Oh, now we're talking!

22
00:03:01,233 --> 00:03:02,442
Wait a second.

23
00:03:02,525 --> 00:03:04,650
This all you've got?

24
00:03:04,733 --> 00:03:06,650
Cut me already.

25
00:03:06,733 --> 00:03:08,567
Let's carve each other--

26
00:03:14,317 --> 00:03:16,733
[FURUTA shrieks]

27
00:03:16,817 --> 00:03:19,983
Ahh, that was painful.

28
00:03:20,067 --> 00:03:22,817
And the chill in
your eyes cut, too.

29
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:24,067
[giggles]

30
00:03:24,150 --> 00:03:26,275
But this is more
like it, I think.

31
00:03:26,358 --> 00:03:29,483
You and I have to put
our very lives on the line.

32
00:03:29,567 --> 00:03:33,858
Or else the game
isn't any fun, you see.

33
00:03:33,942 --> 00:03:36,400
The best things in
life are dangerous.

34
00:03:36,483 --> 00:03:38,900
That's especially
true for games.

35
00:03:38,983 --> 00:03:40,608
And when you think about it,

36
00:03:40,692 --> 00:03:44,275
we're all just pawns
on a great board.

37
00:03:44,358 --> 00:03:45,900
Now...

38
00:03:49,025 --> 00:03:52,067
[FURUTA] ...I think I'd like
to play a game of house.

39
00:03:52,150 --> 00:03:52,983
Come on.

40
00:03:53,067 --> 00:03:55,067
Let's play.

41
00:04:08,358 --> 00:04:09,442
[MARUDE]
Ugh!

42
00:04:09,525 --> 00:04:11,358
How many of these
bastards are out there?

43
00:04:24,192 --> 00:04:27,233
[FURUTA] This is exhilarating,
don't you think?

44
00:04:29,442 --> 00:04:30,775
Die!

45
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:40,150
I said to die.

46
00:04:40,233 --> 00:04:41,942
You trash.

47
00:04:42,025 --> 00:04:46,650
[KANEKI]
You really are strong, Furuta.

48
00:04:46,733 --> 00:04:48,233
You know.

49
00:04:48,317 --> 00:04:51,733
I'm not half as graceful as you.

50
00:04:51,817 --> 00:04:53,317
I'm not smart either.

51
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,942
Or powerful.

52
00:04:56,025 --> 00:04:57,775
Against you.

53
00:04:57,858 --> 00:05:00,858
I couldn't protect the world.

54
00:05:00,942 --> 00:05:05,275
I couldn't even protect
my own tiny little part of it.

55
00:05:05,358 --> 00:05:09,608
Up to now,
all I've done is lose.

56
00:05:09,692 --> 00:05:11,858
You're better.

57
00:05:11,942 --> 00:05:14,525
But this time I'll come through.

58
00:05:14,608 --> 00:05:18,150
I'll beat you
and protect the others.

59
00:05:18,233 --> 00:05:21,275
Humans and ghouls.

60
00:05:32,150 --> 00:05:33,358
Huh?

61
00:05:40,650 --> 00:05:42,733
[FURUTA]
Damn it!

62
00:05:42,817 --> 00:05:45,150
Come on, Special Investigator.

63
00:05:45,233 --> 00:05:48,442
You really think you have
the right to play the hero?

64
00:05:48,525 --> 00:05:51,067
To pretend that you
meant well all along?

65
00:05:51,150 --> 00:05:53,650
I don't buy it!

66
00:05:53,733 --> 00:05:56,067
It was a screwed-up world
we lived in before,

67
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:57,900
but you've made it even worse!

68
00:05:57,983 --> 00:06:01,233
Don't you remember
what you did to Tokyo?

69
00:06:01,317 --> 00:06:02,692
What of that?

70
00:06:02,775 --> 00:06:04,442
What of the countless
innocent lives you've crushed

71
00:06:04,525 --> 00:06:06,692
beneath your boots?

72
00:06:06,775 --> 00:06:09,817
Not just humans, either.

73
00:06:10,608 --> 00:06:13,400
Exactly how many ghouls
do you think you've eaten?

74
00:06:13,483 --> 00:06:15,942
I would wager that you
lost count quite a long time

75
00:06:16,025 --> 00:06:18,025
before you finally stopped.

76
00:06:18,108 --> 00:06:20,650
And largely thanks
to your myriad of failures,

77
00:06:20,733 --> 00:06:23,900
I've had a wonderful time of it.

78
00:06:23,983 --> 00:06:26,733
You tried to fight against
an incarnation of brutality,

79
00:06:26,817 --> 00:06:30,358
but practically
became one yourself.

80
00:06:30,442 --> 00:06:33,067
That little coffee shop
you tried to protect.

81
00:06:33,150 --> 00:06:34,650
Where is it now?

82
00:06:34,733 --> 00:06:37,317
And how's the false family
you tried so desperately

83
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:41,650
to hold together, back
when your name was Haise?

84
00:06:41,733 --> 00:06:42,900
Even after that,

85
00:06:42,983 --> 00:06:45,942
you had the blind gall
to name yourself king.

86
00:06:46,025 --> 00:06:49,483
To let a whole people
put their trust in you.

87
00:06:49,567 --> 00:06:50,692
But you failed.

88
00:06:50,775 --> 00:06:51,525
Yeah.

89
00:06:51,608 --> 00:06:53,108
At everything you've tried!

90
00:06:53,192 --> 00:06:54,108
Hey.

91
00:06:54,192 --> 00:06:56,192
At least you put
on a show for me.

92
00:06:56,275 --> 00:06:58,025
Your failures reassured me

93
00:06:58,108 --> 00:07:02,067
that no matter what we do,
some things can't be changed!

94
00:07:02,150 --> 00:07:03,317
It's true!

95
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,483
You'll make a mess of
things today as well.

96
00:07:05,567 --> 00:07:09,275
Soon enough, it will all
be flushed down the drain!

97
00:07:09,358 --> 00:07:10,983
[giggles]

98
00:07:16,192 --> 00:07:17,858
Is that what you want?

99
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:22,150
Why do you have
that look in your eyes?

100
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:27,025
Don't tell me you think that I'm
the one at a disadvantage here.

101
00:07:27,108 --> 00:07:30,525
You're an honest to goodness
riot, you know that?

102
00:07:30,608 --> 00:07:32,733
It's just not enough.

103
00:07:32,817 --> 00:07:36,067
I wiped the Washu clan
from the face of the earth.

104
00:07:36,150 --> 00:07:39,567
I took the reins of the
CCG and drove it to ruin.

105
00:07:39,650 --> 00:07:42,108
I unleashed the dragon
that ravaged the earth

106
00:07:42,192 --> 00:07:45,692
and claimed countless
thousands of lives.

107
00:07:45,775 --> 00:07:48,192
But it's still not enough!

108
00:07:48,275 --> 00:07:49,650
I want more.

109
00:07:49,733 --> 00:07:51,525
I need more.

110
00:07:51,608 --> 00:07:54,733
So much more!

111
00:07:54,817 --> 00:07:57,483
Give me everything!

112
00:08:09,733 --> 00:08:10,900
[FURUTA]
More!

113
00:08:14,442 --> 00:08:15,692
[FURUTA]
More!

114
00:08:17,275 --> 00:08:18,358
[FURUTA]
More!

115
00:08:20,817 --> 00:08:22,733
[FURUTA]
More!

116
00:08:22,817 --> 00:08:23,900
More!

117
00:08:23,983 --> 00:08:28,233
Give me everything!

118
00:09:43,275 --> 00:09:44,900
[TSUKIYAMA]
Monsieur Naki!

119
00:09:44,983 --> 00:09:46,817
Let's give 'em hell, boys.

120
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:48,400
Go crazy!

121
00:09:48,483 --> 00:09:49,608
[ALL]
Yeah!

122
00:09:49,692 --> 00:09:51,275
Don't go too crazy.

123
00:09:51,358 --> 00:09:52,442
We're still healing.

124
00:09:52,525 --> 00:09:57,983
[FURUTA]
♪ Kagome... Kagome... ♪

125
00:09:58,067 --> 00:10:00,650
♪ The bird in the cage. ♪

126
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:04,567
♪ Bird in the cage. ♪

127
00:10:04,650 --> 00:10:10,317
♪ When, oh when,
will it come out? ♪

128
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:12,067
Tell me Haise.

129
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:18,733
Don't you ever feel like
all of this is just pointless?

130
00:10:18,817 --> 00:10:20,775
Living and dying.

131
00:10:20,858 --> 00:10:24,025
Creating and consuming.

132
00:10:27,817 --> 00:10:30,275
There's no value in it.

133
00:10:30,358 --> 00:10:33,317
There's no reason for it.

134
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:36,275
None of it's worth the trouble.

135
00:10:38,067 --> 00:10:39,358
[FURUTA]
We're all just children,

136
00:10:39,442 --> 00:10:41,942
and the world, a box of toys.

137
00:10:42,025 --> 00:10:44,358
We play for as long
as we're allowed.

138
00:10:44,442 --> 00:10:48,692
And when our time is up,
there's nothing we can do.

139
00:10:48,775 --> 00:10:51,192
The box is closed to us.

140
00:10:51,275 --> 00:10:53,942
Never to be opened again.

141
00:10:54,025 --> 00:10:59,192
I feel sorry for you,
Associate Special Investigator.

142
00:10:59,275 --> 00:11:01,150
You keep clawing
forward through the muck

143
00:11:01,233 --> 00:11:03,233
of this worthless earth.

144
00:11:03,317 --> 00:11:06,317
And you've made it all this way,
through sheer effort.

145
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:10,483
If you didn't happen to cross
paths with Rize when you did.

146
00:11:10,567 --> 00:11:13,733
You never would've had to
take on all that responsibility,

147
00:11:13,817 --> 00:11:15,692
not to mention your suffering.

148
00:11:15,775 --> 00:11:18,233
Right?

149
00:11:18,317 --> 00:11:20,108
[KANEKI]
Furuta.

150
00:11:20,192 --> 00:11:21,650
Look.

151
00:11:21,733 --> 00:11:25,983
I was a nobody, with nothing
to set me apart from the crowd.

152
00:11:26,067 --> 00:11:28,317
Not a thing.

153
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:31,442
But that changed
after I met Rize.

154
00:11:31,525 --> 00:11:34,733
We talked about books and then--

155
00:11:34,817 --> 00:11:37,900
Well that's when I started
to become who I am.

156
00:11:37,983 --> 00:11:40,150
It's when I learned
what true pain was.

157
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:42,275
How to fight for my life.

158
00:11:42,358 --> 00:11:44,525
I've lost a lot since then.

159
00:11:44,608 --> 00:11:46,858
I've failed a lot.

160
00:11:51,442 --> 00:11:55,650
[KANEKI] But... I also
found a place for myself.

161
00:11:55,733 --> 00:11:58,067
I found teachers and friends.

162
00:11:58,150 --> 00:11:59,442
I found allies.

163
00:11:59,525 --> 00:12:00,858
Comrades.

164
00:12:00,942 --> 00:12:03,192
I found love.

165
00:12:03,275 --> 00:12:06,233
And after all the
mistakes I've made.

166
00:12:06,317 --> 00:12:10,692
After being hurt
as badly as I have.

167
00:12:10,775 --> 00:12:14,692
I could never believe
that it was all for nothing.

168
00:12:19,483 --> 00:12:21,525
Wait. I know you.

169
00:12:21,608 --> 00:12:24,233
You're Matsuri Washu!

170
00:12:29,442 --> 00:12:30,900
[KANEKI]
So yeah.

171
00:12:30,983 --> 00:12:32,567
Even if I'd known everything

172
00:12:32,650 --> 00:12:36,025
I would have to go
through because of it,

173
00:12:36,108 --> 00:12:38,108
I'd do it again.

174
00:12:38,192 --> 00:12:41,317
I still would've
gone to see Rize.

175
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:48,942
I'd keep it the same, cause it
all helped get me where I am.

176
00:12:49,025 --> 00:12:53,150
And one more thing.

177
00:12:53,233 --> 00:12:55,858
I know this world can be harsh.

178
00:12:55,942 --> 00:13:01,483
But I don't think it's
screwed up, it just, is.

179
00:13:01,567 --> 00:13:04,108
And even supposing that someday,

180
00:13:04,192 --> 00:13:07,192
everything does
go down the drain.

181
00:13:07,275 --> 00:13:12,275
I'll keep on struggling,
just like I did today.

182
00:13:12,358 --> 00:13:14,983
You're one of the only
people I've come across

183
00:13:15,067 --> 00:13:17,233
I just don't get.

184
00:13:17,317 --> 00:13:19,025
Oh well.

185
00:13:19,108 --> 00:13:22,192
I'll be dead in a moment anyway.

186
00:13:22,275 --> 00:13:23,858
How fucked is that?

187
00:13:23,942 --> 00:13:26,233
It's seriously fucked.

188
00:13:26,317 --> 00:13:31,650
Just like everything else
in this god-forsaken world.

189
00:13:33,900 --> 00:13:36,567
Tell me, Investigator.

190
00:13:36,650 --> 00:13:39,358
If I said that
all I really wanted

191
00:13:39,442 --> 00:13:41,525
was to live a normal life,

192
00:13:41,608 --> 00:13:43,858
you would laugh, wouldn't you?

193
00:13:43,942 --> 00:13:45,817
Huh?

194
00:13:47,942 --> 00:13:50,775
[KANEKI]
No.

195
00:13:53,692 --> 00:13:56,567
[FURUTA laughs]

196
00:13:56,650 --> 00:13:57,900
Ready or not!

197
00:13:57,983 --> 00:13:59,983
[RIZE]
Not! I'm not!

198
00:14:01,858 --> 00:14:03,900
Hey, Rize.

199
00:14:03,983 --> 00:14:05,692
[RIZE]
Hmm?

200
00:14:05,775 --> 00:14:07,567
Don't change.

201
00:14:07,650 --> 00:14:10,900
I hope that when I'm an old man
and you're an old woman,

202
00:14:10,983 --> 00:14:13,900
we'll still be the same.

203
00:14:13,983 --> 00:14:15,650
[RIZE]
That's sweet, Nimura.

204
00:14:15,733 --> 00:14:18,692
But I don't really wanna
become an old woman, you know?

205
00:14:18,775 --> 00:14:20,150
[FURUTA]
Oh, you don't?

206
00:14:20,233 --> 00:14:21,317
Well, I do.

207
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:24,400
I think it'll be fun.

208
00:14:24,483 --> 00:14:26,525
Mm-hmm.

209
00:14:26,608 --> 00:14:29,650
I'm sure it would've been.

210
00:14:59,483 --> 00:15:01,400
[MARUDE]
Attention all personnel.

211
00:15:01,483 --> 00:15:03,775
The fighting is over.

212
00:15:03,858 --> 00:15:05,400
We've won.

213
00:15:05,483 --> 00:15:07,692
Now attend to the wounded.

214
00:15:07,775 --> 00:15:09,025
Repeat.

215
00:15:09,108 --> 00:15:11,025
The fighting is over.

216
00:15:11,108 --> 00:15:12,692
We've won.

217
00:15:12,775 --> 00:15:14,983
Now attend to the wounded.

218
00:16:07,525 --> 00:16:08,608
[KIMI]
Kaneki.

219
00:16:08,692 --> 00:16:10,108
You've almost made it.

220
00:16:10,192 --> 00:16:12,150
The core should be
right above you now.

221
00:16:12,233 --> 00:16:13,483
Please hurry.

222
00:16:15,442 --> 00:16:16,983
[HIDE]
Good luck.

223
00:16:17,067 --> 00:16:19,358
Make sure you come back.

224
00:16:26,817 --> 00:16:27,942
[KANEKI]
We lose.

225
00:16:28,025 --> 00:16:29,400
We take.

226
00:16:29,483 --> 00:16:31,858
We catch and get caught.

227
00:16:31,942 --> 00:16:35,983
We conform and
we make others conform.

228
00:16:36,067 --> 00:16:39,358
We do nothing but cycle
between those roles.

229
00:16:39,442 --> 00:16:43,108
Take what we can and fight not
to lose more than we must.

230
00:16:43,192 --> 00:16:46,317
But as hard as we fight,
we will lose it all.

231
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:50,025
The people we loved
and were loved by will die.

232
00:16:50,108 --> 00:16:51,650
No matter what.

233
00:16:51,733 --> 00:16:54,692
Someday we'll be forgotten.

234
00:16:54,775 --> 00:16:57,775
To live is to be unhappy.

235
00:16:57,858 --> 00:16:59,442
It's futile.

236
00:16:59,525 --> 00:17:01,317
Even so,

237
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:04,442
small and grotesque as I am.

238
00:17:04,525 --> 00:17:08,192
Short and cruel
as this life may be.

239
00:17:08,275 --> 00:17:10,817
I still claw forward.

240
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:13,983
I still search for beauty.

241
00:17:14,067 --> 00:17:15,775
Because...

242
00:17:15,858 --> 00:17:17,858
...it's worth it.

243
00:17:17,942 --> 00:17:20,275
To keep choosing.

244
00:17:20,358 --> 00:17:23,775
To keep being chosen.

245
00:17:40,567 --> 00:17:44,775
[KANEKI]
Farewell, Rize.

246
00:17:58,942 --> 00:18:00,525
[KANEKI]
Thank you.

247
00:19:07,108 --> 00:19:09,192
[RIZE]
Hey.

248
00:19:09,275 --> 00:19:11,525
Kaneki.

249
00:19:11,608 --> 00:19:12,733
You know.

250
00:19:15,442 --> 00:19:18,317
[RIZE] I've been watching
you for a long time.

251
00:19:19,608 --> 00:19:21,150
[NISHIO]
Kaneki!

252
00:19:21,233 --> 00:19:22,733
[HINAMI]
Big Brother!

253
00:19:22,817 --> 00:19:23,650
[URIE]
Sasaki!

254
00:19:23,733 --> 00:19:24,567
[TSUKIYAMA]
Kaneki!

255
00:19:24,650 --> 00:19:25,358
[AKIRA]
Haise!

256
00:19:25,442 --> 00:19:25,942
[YOMO]
Ken!

257
00:19:26,025 --> 00:19:27,192
[BANJO]
Kaneki!

258
00:19:27,275 --> 00:19:27,942
[AYATO]
Kaneki.

259
00:19:28,025 --> 00:19:28,733
[SHIRAZU]
Mr. Sass!

260
00:19:28,817 --> 00:19:29,400
[SAIKO]
Maman!

261
00:19:29,483 --> 00:19:30,942
[MUTSUKI]
Teach!

262
00:19:31,025 --> 00:19:32,108
[ARIMA]
Haise.

263
00:19:33,817 --> 00:19:34,983
[HIDE]
Kaneki.

264
00:19:38,733 --> 00:19:40,400
[TOUKA]
Kaneki.

